HEADWORD: Introvenient
<hw>In`tro*ven"ient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>introveniens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>introvenire</ets> to come in;
<ets>intro</ets> within + <ets>venire</ets> to come.]</ety> <def>Coming
in together; entering; commingling.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir
T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
